				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Need help finishing Epic<a name="73255"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 15 05 1:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>What level are you?  I have soloed Fear and Phinney and I am only 65 and had less than 40 AA's spent.  If you want to drop Phinney easy, depending on your level, you can group with a wizzy or mag.  they need drops off of him also.  Invis to the bottom and fight him in the pit.  The seahorses won't aggro down there.  Pull him with dispell and make sure you pulse him at least twice with it.  Have wizzy and mag nuke the heck out of him.  He should drop in less than a min.  did that with me (65 bard) and a 65 wizzy last night.  He needs to be dispelled though, he does have a few buffs.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Fear, need Fade at least to solo this part.  If not, get a good strong group or mini raid, and just pull from the temple.
<br />
I had to do about 3 pulls from temple (solo) and charm swarm kite my way until I got the warriors to come out.  Tendril dropped on the 3rd or 4th one.
<br />

<br />
Can't help you with the dragon scales, bought the white one (15k), and guildie got a red one for me.
<br />

<br />
Haven't done trak yet, cause I need to do the turn in items for the lute to give to the udb to spawn the right trak.
<br />

<br />
Basically what I heard about trak, is now he is very 1 groupable.  I probably will try to get 1 tank, 1 cleric, and then nukers.  Wizzies or mages with pets.  Basically need to do about 30k of damage in about 30 secs.  Please correct me if I am wrong about this.</span></td>
