				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Need help finishing Epic<a name="73285"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 15 05 10:51 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>ok I did fear when I was 65.   I also couldnt get much help. I made due with the help I did get.  I went in with a sing group made up of 65 chanter 2x 65 mage's and a 65 BL.  We went in after a major guild raided and killed all the named and CT.  We went in after normal mobs repoped.  named and CT have much longer respawn.  We broke the zone in fairly easy. and moved to the north west corner camp just west of the temple.  I made sure and cleared most of the wanders in the lower part of the zone so when I pulled from the temple I had a place to run to.  Now the strategy I used was when I pulled from the temple and all the amy's aggro'd I pulled then south away toward the zone in and mezed them along the way to separate them and then had the mage call of hero me back to the group to lose aggro. I then waited tillthe main group went back into the temple and then pulled the stragglers that i mezzed back to the group.  I repeated till I got my drop.  The key to this strategy was the mage and the need to have the named and CT killed previously.  The mobs in this zone arent too tough at 65,but they do aggro one another and the chanter helped but was not key to my success.
<br />
It can be done with one group at 65 with the right strategy.
<br />
Hope this was a help,
<br />
Naymin 65 Bard on XEV
<br />
BTW I bought the dragon scales in the bazaar. 9k for the red and 11k the white
<br />
</span></td>
