				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Need help finishing Epic<a name="73514"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 21 05 9:25 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I soloed in Fear from lvl 57 till 59, can be done but it takes a lot of effort to learn pathing and (huge) agro range on stuff.
<br />

<br />
If anything that DT is near zone-in you can forget it but otherwise you can get in and do it, just have high resists versus magic/disease to stop snares and fear.
<br />

<br />
SLowly clear a small corner, lower lvl charm works on a lot of the rabble near zone in so you can semi-charm kite/swarm kite to clear stuff.
<br />

<br />
Then chant-kite and resist songs slowly along the left wall untill you get to the castle, use sneak to get in and reduce initial agro.
<br />

<br />
Check server tick, cast someone insta clicky that agroes if you have one or time a dispell very well and you get only a few mobs from castle, chant-kite, rinse and repeat at nauseum.
<br />

<br />
With the summon corpses it gets tons easier since you don't have to worry about loosing a corpse before rezz timer expires.
<br />
I lost about 4 corpses worth of rezzes in POF as dracolich was camping the zone in or one of the golems got pulled to nearby the zone in and was stuck on the geometry at one of the nearby buildings (the suck, zone-in and get dt before you have cleared the zone in :()</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
